    "raw": "Shadup DB stores every path that leads to a content-addressed blob (more visible for JPEGs than FLAC). There is no historical-rename / effective-dating model yet.\n\nResearch best ways to store path provenance over time (start/end effective dates, or equivalent), then implement two effects:\n\n1. `shadup mv` \u2014 rename targets on disk and record the change in the DB as end/start path entries.\n2. `shadup reconcile` (name TBD) \u2014 paths that no longer exist get end-dates; newly seen paths get new entries with start and open end.\n\nConstraints / context:\n- Content under data/ stays hash-addressed; this is about path rows pointing at hashes.\n- correct-flac-names will rename album dirs under files/; need a supported way to keep DB paths in sync (mv bookkeeping vs post-hoc reconcile).\n- No concept of historical renames today \u2014 design should not require rewriting history of old DBs without a migration story.\n\nNote: if start/end path history lands in shadup, we do **not** need to abuse `.meta.johan.json` (`original-album-name`) as rename history \u2014 that field is a stopgap for human/provenance until the DB can answer \u201cwhat paths ever pointed at this hash.\u201d Prefer shadup history; drop or stop writing the johan workaround once mv/reconcile exist."
  },
